## tool-llm-list: llm_list tool definition

### llm_list() â†’ str
List all registered LLM models with their full details.

Returns for each model: name, type (OPENAI/GEMINI), model_id, host, max_context,
tool_call_available (YES/NO), llm_call_timeout, and description.

When to use:
- Before calling llm_call_clean, to find a model with tool_call_available=YES.
- When the user asks which LLM models are available or what their capabilities are.
